   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The three operational buttons are placed to
the left of the display and numpad keys. All the numpad keys are used
to enter the respective number in an input field, for example when
setting a value.</p>
            <fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="../Images/MM_PxW_WxW_SDC_Front-Panel-All_A-T_0000356100.svg"
                      placement="inline"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </sectiondiv>
         <table pgwide="1" class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="20.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="40.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="4.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Position</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Name</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test
button</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to test all the LEDs on the front panel.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for two seconds to turn
off the system.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press for one second to turn on the system.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The display of the system interface. By default, the current operating
mode is displayed.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow up key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Used to navigate up between the selections in the system interface.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press together with some numerical keys for additional options<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> or measurements</ph>.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(F)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow down
key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Used to navigate down between the selections in the system interface.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(G)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to enter the user stack.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">In the user stack, press to
confirm an option when using the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> to cycle between options.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(H)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Mute key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to mute the audible alarm (horn). Any new alarms will activate
the audible alarm again.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(I)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to confirm alarms, for more info see <xref href="Alarm_Panel_CPT_0000356320.dita#AlarmPanel-83C303AF/AlarmConfirmationReset-D39B4898"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to cycle between
options for a selection in the interface.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(J)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Star/number
0 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Used to deactivate a mode/setting or decline a selection in the interface.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to enter the alarm stack.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow up key</b> to enter the event log.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(K)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Used to exit a menu in the interface or to erase the latest entry
if keying in a number.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(L)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number
1 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to display the current date and time.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Used to activate
a mode/setting or confirm a selection in the interface.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press
together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 2 key</b> to open the password input,
for example to reset the event log.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(M)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 2 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the inverter current.</p>
                        <p platform="SDC" class="- topic/p ">If a battery sensor is installed, press to display
the battery temperature.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number
1 key</b> to open the password input, for example to reset the event
log.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(N)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 3 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the output frequency.</p>
                        <p platform="SDC" class="- topic/p ">—</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(O)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 4 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the mains current in the display.</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">—</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(P)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the battery current in the display.</p>
                        <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow up key</b> to display the total DC current.</p>
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">If a battery
sensor is installed, press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to
display the battery temperature.</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press to display
the DC current in the display.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(Q)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 6 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to display the output current in the display.</p>
                        <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow up key</b> to
display the output peak current.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(R)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 7 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the mains voltage in the display.</p>
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">Press together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow up key</b> to
display the bypass mains voltage (Mains 2).</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press
to display the bypass mains voltage (Mains 2).</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(S)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the DC / battery voltage in the
display.</p>
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">If a battery sensor is installed, press
together with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to display battery temperature.</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">Press to display the DC voltage in the display.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(T)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press to display the output voltage in the display.<fn platform="SDC" class="- topic/fn "> As an option, it is possible to indicate half of the battery voltage
for asymmetrical monitoring.</fn>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(U)</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Common alarm</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The common alarm LED indicates that there is at least one active
alarm in the system. For more information see the chapter <xref href="Alarm_Stack_and_Event_Log_CPT_0000333859.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        <note class="- topic/note ">There are a few alarms that does not affect the
common alarm.</note>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
